In Python, indexing is an easy and convenient way to slice a string.

Syntax

string[start:end:step]

e.g.
# Python program to demonstrate
# string slicing
  
# String slicing 
String ='ASTRING'
  
# Using indexing sequence
print(String[:3])
print(String[1:5:2])
print(String[-1:-12:-2])
  
# Prints string in reverse 
print("\nReverse String")
print(String[::-1])


#### Output:
AST
SR
GITA

Reverse String
GNIRTSA
